      "name": "Product Info",
      "settings": {
        "width": "page",
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/8-chef-knife-ji-series-x08-2690091.jpg",
        "header_type": "left",
        "heading": "<h2>Proprietary steel. Exclusive to Xinzuo.</h2>",
        "content": "<p>12Cr18MoV is Xinzuo's proprietary composition — higher chromium (18%) for superior corrosion resistance, with molybdenum and vanadium for toughness and edge retention. Not available from any other brand.</p>",
        "icon_block_state": true,
        "first_num": "3",
        "second_num": "3",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-5",
        "padding_top": 80,
        "padding_bottom": 80
      }
    },
    "product_info2_8biKrj": {
      "type": "product-info2",
      "name": "Product Info2",
      "settings": {
        "width": "page",
        "heading_title": "PROPRIETARY STEEL. PROVEN PERFORMANCE.",
        "heading_content": "<h2>An Edge You Can't Get Anywhere Else</h2>",
        "header_type": "left",
        "background_type": "none",
        "block_type": "text",
        "block_position": "below",
        "heading_footer": "The Ji Series uses steel that Xinzuo developed exclusively — 12Cr18MoV. The higher chromium content (18% vs 15% in VG10-class steels) provides noticeably better corrosion resistance for cooks who work with acidic ingredients daily.",
        "image_video": "image",
        "image_width": 0,
        "image_height": 440,
        "image_width_mobile": 0,
        "color_scheme": "scheme-5",
        "footer_state": "visible",
        "footer_type": "first",
        "footer_left": "<h2>BEYOND STANDARD DAMASCUS</h2>",
        "footer_right": "<p>While most Damascus series use 10Cr15CoMoV, the Ji Series steps up to a proprietary composition with enhanced corrosion performance. The trade-off is slightly lower maximum hardness (59-61 vs 60-62 HRC), but the result is a blade that's easier to maintain and more forgiving in daily use.</p>",
        "padding_top": 80,
        "padding_bottom": 80,
        "additional_footer": false,
        "additional_content1": "",
        "additional_content2": ""
      }
    },
    "product_info2_eVwTgB": {
      "type": "product-info2",
      "name": "Product Info2",
      "settings": {
        "width": "full",
        "heading_title": "Handle Design",
        "heading_content": "<h2>Ebony Wood<br/>Timeless Elegance</h2>",
        "header_type": "center",
        "background_type": "none",
        "block_type": "text",
        "block_position": "below",
        "heading_footer": "Ebony is one of the world's most prized handle woods — dense, naturally water-resistant, and incredibly smooth. Its deep black color provides a dramatic contrast to the Damascus steel blade. Each handle is hand-shaped and polished to showcase the wood's natural character.",
        "image_video": "image",
        "image_width": 0,
        "image_height": 440,
        "image_width_mobile": 0,
        "color_scheme": "scheme-5",
        "footer_state": "visible",
        "footer_type": "first",
        "footer_left": "",
        "footer_right": "<h2>Dense</h2><p>Ebony resists moisture and wear naturally.</p><h2>Dark</h2><p>Deep black color contrasts beautifully with Damascus steel.</p><h2>Durable</h2><p>One of the hardest woods on earth — built to last a lifetime.</p>",
        "padding_top": 80,
        "padding_bottom": 80,
        "additional_footer": false,
        "additional_content1": "",
        "additional_content2": ""
      }
    },
    "product_info2_GjRq8Y": {
      "type": "product-info2",
      "name": "Product Info2",
      "settings": {
        "width": "page",
        "heading_title": "",
        "heading_content": "<h2>Why Choose the<br/>Ji Series</h2>",
        "header_type": "center",
        "background_type": "none",
        "block_type": "text",
        "block_position": "below",
        "heading_footer": "",
        "image_video": "image",
        "image_width": 0,
        "image_height": 440,
        "image_width_mobile": 0,
        "color_scheme": "scheme-5",
        "footer_state": "visible",
        "footer_type": "third",
        "footer_left": "<p>With 18 knife types — the widest selection in the entire Xinzuo range — the Ji Series covers every kitchen task. From a 4-inch paring knife to a 10-inch carving knife, plus specialty blades like the bone chopper, cleaver, and Viking knife, there's a Ji for every cut.</p>",
        "footer_right": "<p>The proprietary 12Cr18MoV steel delivers corrosion resistance that surpasses standard Damascus series, making the Ji ideal for cooks who work with citrus, tomatoes, and other acidic ingredients. Ebony handles add a premium, timeless aesthetic.</p>",
        "padding_top": 80,
        "padding_bottom": 80,
        "additional_footer": false,
        "additional_content1": "",
        "additional_content2": ""
      }
    },
